00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,079
Let's make a toast.

35
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,320
Mr. Chai,

36
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,040
why didn't you bring Xiaoyu today?

37
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,960
I called her, but she didn't pick up.

38
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,680
Then, I thought, I'm having dinner with Mr. Ma

39
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,800
instead of any client.

40
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:14,400
Right.

41
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,040
So that's fine.

42
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,840
Then you made a mistake.

43
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:18,880
Without Xiaoyu,

44
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,720
you'll get wasted sooner than Mr. Ma.

45
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,560
That's true.

46
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:22,800
He can actually drink.

47
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:24,600
Shanshan,

48
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,600
tell you what,

49
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,800
have you noticed

50
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:30,240
that everyone drinks less in a business dinner?

51
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,320
Why?

52
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,720
Because everyone is careful.

53
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,760
They are afraid of falling into a trap.

54
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,320
Therefore,

55
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:40,240
it's always easier to have dinner with friends.

56
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,640
We can drink as much as we want,

57
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,440
right?

58
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:44,200
Here, my friend. Here's a toast to you.

59
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:45,920
Mr. Chai, here's to you.

60
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:46,480
Of course.

61
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,120
My pleasure.

62
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,000
Ms. Writer.

63
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,240
My pleasure.

64
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:51,840
Such an honor.

65
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,480
Shanshan, I feel that you're not yourself today.

66
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,160
You drank even less than me.

67
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,200
Why do you look so disoriented?

68
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,760
She's just tired.

69
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,520
Actually, that's not the only reason.

70
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,920
Feng Xi took some days off.

71
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,840
So I had to be here every day.

72
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,200
I thought

73
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:14,000
that nothing goes wrong
even if I have eight companies.

74
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,560
Let alone a restaurant.

75
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:18,200
But then, everything turned out wrong.

76
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,120
Everyone has their own area of expertise.

77
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,120
Even though you have eight companies,

78
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,840
your teams are well-trained.

79
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,640
So you only need to tell them what to do.

80
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:27,960
What is catering?

81
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,680
It covers everything.

82
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,360
It requires hard work.

83
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,440
Most of the time, you're a hands-off boss.

84
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,560
Why do you think you can do this?

85
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:36,400
You're right.

86
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,720
In the last couple of days,

87
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,960
I was suddenly impressed
by what Feng Xi had been doing.

88
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,520
It's not something that anyone can do.

89
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,800
She has been doing this for a year or so.

90
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,080
I must make a toast to her now.

91
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:45,880
Me too.

92
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,680
To Feng Xi.

93
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,240
Even though I haven't met Feng Xi,

94
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,159
I'd like to drink to her, too.

95
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,400
Here, let's raise our glasses.

96
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,280
To Feng Xi.

97
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,040
Shanshan,

98
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,880
you have eight companies?

99
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,000
Tell you what, Mr. Ma,

100
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,840
this friend of mine

101
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,160
is just talented in every way.

102
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,160
Mm.

103
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,840
I'm a nobody compared with Mr. Ma.

104
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,280
Mr. Ma, Mr. Chai told me

105
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:10,920
that you created a miracle the first time

106
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,120
you entered show business.

107
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,040
He bought four novels at a low price

108
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,280
and all of them went viral.

109
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,880
He made loads of money

110
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,080
by selling the rights of adaptation.

111
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,040
I was just lucky.

112
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,960
It was luck.

113
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,600
Come on.

114
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,800
We all do business.

115
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,200
We know better than others
that there isn't such thing as luck.

116
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:30,840
It's all about your ability.

117
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,800
There's nothing wrong

118
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,240
with Shanshan's words.

119
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:37,000
Why is Mr. Ma successful in this field?

120
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:40,640
Because he is a middle-aged art boy himself.

121
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:42,920
Right, middle-aged.

122
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,960
He is a bookworm.

123
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:46,440
Therefore, as soon as he reads it,

124
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,960
he'll know whether it's a good story or not.

125
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,440
It sounds like

126
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:53,080
an opportunity is right in front of me.

127
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:54,040
What do you mean?

128
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,920
This friend of mine is a woman of letters.

129
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,120
She writes fairy tales.

130
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:00,800
Mr. Ma,

131
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,560
could you take a look at her works

132
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,520
and give her a chance if there's any?

133
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:05,480
Of course.

134
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:06,640
No problem at all.

135
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,000
Thanks, Mr. Ma.

136
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,080
Cheers.

137
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:14,800
Take it slow.

138
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,400
I can't drive you home today.

139
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,960
I rarely have a chance to relax.

140
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,120
The last time I got drunk

141
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,760
was before I had my second child.

142
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,400
She reminds me of the old days.

143
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,720
Mr. Ma,

144
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,400
when we were fresh out of college,

145
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:30,800
each time we got together,

146
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,760
remember what we did after getting drunk?

147
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,680
Reciting poems.

148
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,520
We could just do that all night.

149
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:41,120
We laughed and cried as we recited poems.

150
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,840
How young we were!

151
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:43,640
Absolutely.

152
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,800
The good old days.

153
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,480
Back then, before we got together for dinner,

154
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,280
we had to prepare three days in advance

155
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,520
in case we went out of poems.

156
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,240
That's right.

157
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,520
Mr. Chai,

158
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,080
I didn't know

159
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,720
this side of you.

160
00:06:59,080 --> 00:06:59,840
Tell you what, Shanshan,

161
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,040
you underestimated me.

162
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,080
When I was young,

163
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,600
I had all poems at my fingertips.

164
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:06,560
Back in college,

165
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,680
you know,

166
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,880
a lot of girls

167
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,640
pursued me.

168
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,360
For what?

169
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,480
To beat you up?

170
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,960
He's not bragging.

171
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:20,080
He was really popular at that time.

172
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,080
So popular.

173
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,120
To be honest,

174
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,200
a line of girls were waiting to pursue him.

175
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,280
He was too busy to deal with everyone.

176
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,120
I was really busy.

177
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,280
What about now?

178
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,920
Mr. Chai is just as popular as before.

179
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,760
He's still got it.

180
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,680
Not bad.

181
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,840
Let me tell you something, Shanshan.

182
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,040
Let me show you my talent.

183
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,240
Please.

184
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,480
Listen carefully.

185
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,440
"How many

186
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:43,720
loved your moments of glad grace,

187
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:47,520
And loved your beauty with love false

188
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,840
or true."

189
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,240
He's looking at you fondly.

190
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,600
Who wrote it?

191
00:07:53,159 --> 00:07:53,800
Who?

192
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,400
Don't stop. Go on.

193
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,880
I forgot the lines. But who?

194
00:07:57,159 --> 00:07:58,800
Don't tell me it's Zhao Zhao.

195
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:01,480
Do you really think I didn't go to college?

196
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,040
It's Yeats' poem.

197
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,760
Good.

198
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,360
Don't praise her yet.

199
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,640
It was an easy one.

200
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,040
So easy.

201
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,000
Let me give you a hard one.

202
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,440
Wait a minute.

203
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,360
You can save yours for later.

204
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,640
Let me do an easy one.

205
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:16,800
Please.

206
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,280
"A ragged urchin,

207
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,800
aimless and alone,

208
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,520
Loitered about that vacancy;

209
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,800
a bird

210
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:29,240
Flew up to safety from his well-aimed stone."

211
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,680
I know this one.

212
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,799
Is it…

213
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,320
Wait.

214
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:34,280
Don't say it.

215
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,000
Who?

216
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,679
I'm so close. Don't say it. It's…

217
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:37,960
W. H. Auden.

218
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:40,120
The Shield of Achilles.

219
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,120
Right, W. H. Auden.

220
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:42,360
I was about to say it.

221
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:42,960
All right.

222
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,200
Stop it.

223
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,240
Don't pretend.

224
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:46,880
See?

225
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,800
I didn't brag at all.

226
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,160
She is good.

227
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,360
Four years of Chinese literature
is not a waste of time.

228
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,160
Absolutely.

229
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,160
"We had dreams back then,

230
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,040
About literature,

231
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,240
About love,

232
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,880
About a journey across the world.

233
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,880
Now deep into the night we drink,

234
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,160
With the clattering sound of glasses

235
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,640
And that of shattered dreams."

236
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:09,720
The Visitor from Poland.

237
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,400
Bei Dao.

238
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,440
All right.

239
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,640
Another round.

240
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,320
Come on.

241
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,560
You must drink two cups.

242
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:17,320
Two, of course.

243
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:22,040
"Time and the bell

244
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,960
have buried the day,

245
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,480
The black cloud carries the sun away.

246
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,160
Will the sunflower turn to us."

247
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,120
No, it won't.

248
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:32,640
I don't know this one.

249
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:34,840
T. S. Eliot.

250
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,680
Yeah.

251
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,800
Come on. Let's drink to this one.

252
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:40,640
Here's to the poet.

253
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,120
Cheers.

254
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:46,960
Honey.

255
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:47,640
You're finally here.

256
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:48,800
What are you doing here?

257
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:52,200
Let me introduce him. This is Du Shijun.

258
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:52,800
Du Shijun.

259
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:53,680
We met before.

260
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:54,640
I'm Chai Yong.

261
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:55,440
This is my husband.

262
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,320
Mr. Chai.

263
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,160
Haven't seen you for a while.

264
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,600
Let me introduce you two.

265
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,000
This is Mr. Ma.

266
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,880
We went to the same college.

267
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:02,680
Take a seat.

268
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,360
Why are you here?

269
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,280
How much have you drunk?

270
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,720
I assume she's got depressed

271
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:07,840
as she always stays at home.

272
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,680
Shut up.

273
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,360
I'm not depressed at all.

274
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,720
I'm so happy.

275
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,560
Let me tell you something.

276
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,280
My husband loves me so much.

277
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:17,800
He even transferred

278
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,240
to another department for me.

279
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,120
Am I right?

280
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:22,920
Mr. Du,

281
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:23,920
you know what,

282
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:26,320
your wife is so talented.

283
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:29,120
She reads a lot.

284
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,440
We were reciting poems.

285
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,400
She knows

286
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,600
much more

287
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,120
than both of us together.

288
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,320
I'm so humbled.

289
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,120
I'm really impressed.

290
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,160
Look how I beat them.

291
